inn1.comm: Right. Here we go. A wide to start of the proceedings. Off side wide, if you are really curious.
full pitched, on the middle and leg and Sibanda leans forward, covers for the angle and defends
chance for a run out. Missed. It was pushed to backward point, yes, no and Fawad Alam fires in a throw but he is not accurate
down the leg side, he tries a whipping flick shot and if you went with the fury of the bat swing, the ball should have sailed over the boundary but then, he didn't make any contact.
in the channel outside off stump and is left alone.

Caught at first slip by Misbah. Oh no. Wait. Did it bounce?  It was slanted across Masakadza who stabbed it low to first slip where Misbah tries to get his fingers around it and he is confident he has caught it cleanly. Masakadza stands his ground and it is refered upstairs. The replays didn't give proper angles to confirm whether it bounced. The benefit of doubt goes to the batsman. If you really put a gun on my head and ask me to make a decision, I think it was OK. It rolled up his fingers but then as I said the replays were not great. Who knows it might have bounced.
down the leg side, attempted a flick shot
another wide down the leg side
ah finally its really over. In the zone outside off, left alone
here we go. Rauf's first delivery. He has been bowling well for the last four years in first-class. Good start. Seaming delivery in the zone outside off stump and is left alone
And again. Open-chested action. Will track his speed from the next ball.

Some swing there. Full pitched and outside off stump, sucked the batsman forward and he went for a cover drive and the ball took it through point.  The  broadcasters are not showing the speed guns . So can't give you the speed.
slips on to the pads and is flicked away
ah we got one here. Around 131 kmph length delivery on the off stump, bit of a heavy ball too and is defended to the leg side
good probing delivery. It cut in a touch, off a length, from just outside off and the batsman jabs at it and gets an inside edge. Not a bad first over that.
fullish, on the middle and leg, turned to mid-on
beaten again. Curving delivery, the one that leaves the right-hand batsman and he is beaten, lunging forward to defend
shuffles across to cover for the angle and pushes to covers. Tanvir doesn't quite bend it back in as much and hence he is shuffling.
tries to get it back in but ends up on the pads and the ball rolls away. The shuffle meant the batsman was not in great position to flick it away.
on the middle and leg and is struck on the thigh pad
cuts in from outside off stump, evades the defensive stroke and strikes high on the pad. But then, its a no-ball.
swing and a miss. In the zone outside off stump and he tried to slog it over mid-on but the bat met air and the ball nestled into the 'keeper's gloves
130 kmph delivery on the middle stump, worked behind square for a single
full pitched on the middle stump line, placed to right of mid-off and well timed too,
tip and run, pushed to extra covers for a quick single
120.6 kmph on the off and middle, tapped to midwicket region and again they are off for the quick single.
shout for lbw but Aleem Dar is not impressed. Good shout too. It landed full in length and came in a touch, the batsman was on the forward lunge and was struck. Perhaps, he was outside the line.
full and wide, reaches out for it and goes for a cover drive. The ball makes contact with the bottom half of the bat and so he doesn't get much power but does get his placement right
sweetly timed this time but good diving stop at covers
from round the stumps, misses a flick shot but no wide signal
fullish, flicked to right of midwicket where Rizwan dives to his right to cut it off.
full pitched, driven to mid-off
leans forward to defend a length delivery to covers
beaten. In the zone outside off and he pushed inside the line
homing in on the off stump and is defended to the off side
131.3 kmph length delivery on the off stump, straightens and is pushed to the leg side.

What a catch to get your first wicket! Don't trust your fielders, take it yourself, says Rauf. Full in length, on the off stump and is driven low to him and Rauf picks it off his shoe laces in one fluent motion.
sharp bouncer, swayed away but he had overstepped the mark. And the speed gun shows 112 kmph. Uff! I don't trust that gun.
moves outside leg and has a slog and all he gets is an inside edge to fine leg region
full and outside off stump, Williams goes for an airy drive and is beaten
126.9 kmph delivery on the off and middle, defended to the off side
cuts in from just outside off stump, beats the intended prod and strikes him on the pad but its going down the leg side and they don't bother appealing
short-pitched delivery and Williams can't connect with his pull shot. It is getting dark out there. Sikhander Bakht, on air, reckons the conditions should favour the seamers
good probing delivery just ouside off, again shaping in but Williams covers his off stump and lets it go past him
beaten. This time, Williams goes for an off drive and the ball cuts in to thread the bat and pad gap but shaves past the off stump
118.8kmph full delivery, just outside off stump and is left alone
beaten. Lovely delivery. The conditions are helping. This one landed on a length, just outside the off stump and shaped away late.
gets this one to move in towards the off stump and is defended on the front foot
full pitched, outside off stump, pushed to covers.
drifts on to the pads and is turned away to fine leg
defended to the off side
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket and again they take a quick single. Their running between the wicket and the fielding has been pretty sharp. They create opportunities on the field.
extra bounce off a good length and a surprised Williams jabs it past gully
beaten. Moves away with the usual Tanvir angle - leaving the right-hand bat- and Sibanda pushes at it
gets behind the line of this one and defends to the off side
testing line outside off stump and Sibanda thinks about driving before shouldering arms
short of length, outside off stump and Sibanda plays a neat crispy on-the-up drive through covers. Great to watch and they run really hard again.
full in length, on the off stump line, Williams is late in pushing at it and gets an inside -edge to the leg side
fullish and on the legs, flicked straight to square leg. He should have put that one away to the boundary.
on the off stump line and is driven to the off side
slanted across the batsman who lets it go through to the 'keeper
on the off stump line, pushed to extra cover and they rush across for a single. It is not picked up cleanly by Nasir and they make it easy
114.4 kmph - hmm I really don't trust this gun, not that Rauf is bowling express pace but he should be hovering near 130 ... -- on the off stump line, defended to the off side
turned to midwicket where Nasir dives but ends up misfielding.
leans forward to defend a delivery around the off stump

Run out by Rizwan from long leg. It was on the pads, clipped past square leg and they tried to push for the second run. Rizwan moved swiftly to his right, swooped and fired in flat and accurate throw. Sarfraz does the rest. Gone!
leans forward to defend
short delivery and is pulled away to long-leg. Taibu is in and this should get interesting as he likes to go for his shots. And it was this pair who did quite well in the last game
creamed through covers. Fab strike. Full pitched and Williams leaned across to drill it through the off-side field
nicely played. It was full and on the middle, Taibu worked his wrists over time, the bottom-hand took control and he whipped it past square leg.
pushed towards mid-on and they take the quick run. Had the throw hit the striker's end, he would have been found short. Didn't miss by much, though.
overpitched delivery again and is driven but straight to mid-off
short and rising, Williams tries to upper cut it but can't connect
slightly slower one, full and outside off, square driven to right of backward point where Fawad Alam pulls off a fine stop. Another no-ball, though. Free hit coming up.
again they don't take full toll of the free hit. He moved outside leg and went for a slog but Rauf pitched it short and the ball bounced over the flashing blade
full and straight, pushed past the bowler
leans forward to push to covers
in the zone outside off stump and is left alone
outside off stump, has a flash and a miss.
pushed outside off again and Taibu lets this one go past him
on the middle and leg, wristed to square leg for a single
placed to right of mid-on
full pitched, on the off stump, Taibu wants to drive it down the ground but gets an inside-edge to square leg
short and wide, slapped but can't beat the cover fielder

Wow! Stunning catch at covers. That man Rizwan again. It was poor delivery - short and wide- and Taibu slashed it in the air but Rizwan took off in the air, left hand outstretched and was parallel to the ground when he took it. Watch it in the Youtube. Coming soon, in a computer near you
on the middle stump line, inside-edge to the leg side
on the stumps, played to the on side
beaten on the cut. It was short and deserved that shot but he couldn't execute it properly
floated on the stumps, worked to midwicket
outside off stump and Williams lets it go
from round the stumps, this one comes in with the arm and Williams gets an inside-edge on to the pads. Good variation there
on the off stump, defended on the front foot
big responsibility now on Williams and he leans forward to defend
drifts down the leg side

Flighted delivery and Williams goes for a slog sweep and misses. Sarfraz whips the bails off in a flash and appeals. It is referred upstairs. The back foot was on the line - the line belongs to the umpire which means that can be given out - but probably just before the bails came off, a part of the foot was dragged inside. The third umpire offers the benefit of doubt to the batsman. But there is certainly something in that breakfast. An enquiry committee needs to be set up!
on the stumps, jabbed to the off side

surprise bouncer from the mediumpacer Riaz and Williams is stunned but recovered well to fend it off to gully. He took the bottom-hand off the handle as he arched back and though he took the eyes off the ball, the soft hands meant the ball didn't travel to waiting palms
played with soft hands again - tapped close on the off side and they pick up a single
full and outside off, dabbed away to third man for a single
on the off stump line, steered to point
punched through cover point. Short of length and Williams forced it on the up through the off side. He takes a leg-stump guard, a bottom-hand grip and keeps his bat raised a touch in the air.
flighted delivery on the off stump line, wristed to square leg for a single
tossed up nicely, slow loopy delivery and Williams has to check his drive and pushes it back to the bowler
leans forward to defend
he is bowling from round the stumps to Williams. This one comes in with the arm and Williams goes back to punch it to the off side
edged away to third man boundary. It was a nice flighted off break and Williams pushed inside the line and got an outside edge. No one in slip, nor silly point. Now then, Why?
stops on the batsman who does well to adjust and roll his wrists over it and send it down towards mid-on region albeit uppishly
137.1 kmph delivery -  in the zone outside off, Williams has a slash and a miss
makes contact with his punchy drive and gets it down to man at deep cover

Williams could have a misty eye now. He has top-edged a pull shot. It was the short one from Riaz - who has shown a penchant to send that delivery now and then - and Williams' pull went awry. Caught at long-leg. Zimbabwe slid further.
sharp delivery 139 kmph - he is getting quicker and quicker after starting off bowling gentle mediumpace. This one kicks up and the batsman sways away
slips in a slower one and Taylor defends on the front foot
turns down the leg side and Ashoka de Silva extends his arms
turn on offer for MAlik. Also helps when the batsmen try to play against the turn. This one breaks in from the off stump and he tries to cover drive and can only get an inside edge to midwicket
goes right back to jab a spinning off break
straighter one outside off and is pushed to left of covers

trapped by a quicker one! That one really zipped through. It landed on a length and seamed on straight, Chibhabha was caught completely by surprise and the ball evaded the intended jab and struck him high on the pad. He was on the back foot but the ball looked high. Zaheer Abbas, on air, reckons it would have gone over.
flighted turning delivery, gets an inside-edge on to the pad
spins down the leg side
shifts his line to outside off and he takes it on the pad, pretending to play an defensive stroke
on a length, just outside off, tapped to the off side
136.1 kmph length delivery from the left-handed Riaz, on the leg and middle and strikes high on the pad.
slower one but again on the leg stump line and hence ineffective. Good though though.
the cloud cover is persisting and the seamers are making good use of it. On the off stump line, pushed to the off side
fuller and Taylor doesn't quite move his feet, just lunges forward to defend
that bouncer arrives and Taylor takes the bottom-hand off the handle and jabs it to  gully.
leans forward to drive to mid-off
it turns in from outside off, gets an inside edge, on the flap of the pad and goes to short backward leg region and Sarfraz makes an desperate attempt to take the catch. Good efffort.
slightly short and is cut to deep point
the turns starts from middle and leg and he turns it to fine leg for a single
starts from outside off, he cuts and gets a profitable outside edge
beaten. Full and moving away, beaten on the defensive stroke

banged in short and just outside off stump and Chigumbura tries to withdraw his bat away from the line but the ball hits the bat and runs away past the first slip fielder. Now a second slip moves in. And i didn't say anything Rohit!
guided to backward point
outside off stump, pushed to the off side
beaten. 134kmph delivery, full and slanting away, has a lame poke
116.3 kmph, length delivery, steered to backward point
outside off stump and is pushed to Nasir at covers. Even before Nasir fields, Sarfraz shouts, "well done Nasir Well done Nasir" Arre!
on the legs, worked to long leg region
full and outside off and driven past covers. Sarfraz again, "Nasir!" but that ball was far away to his left
turns in from outside off and strikes the pad
good spin on offer here. But Malik starts from middle stump and so this one goes down leg
flighted on the stumps, worked to midwicket
slows up the pace and again turned to midwicket
full and on the middle stump line, defended to the off side
on the stumps, turned to the on side
short of length, on the off stump line and is pushed back to the bowler
fuller, 136.5 kmph, just outside off, steered to backward point region
that bouncer again, again Taylor is hurried and jabs at it. It rams into the gloves and drops down on the off side
another bouncer - the speed gun says 111kmph - and this time Taylor drops his wrists and sways away
flighted delivery, driven back to Malik. "Lovely bowling," says Sarfraz before adding, "Bahut aala bahut aala"
floated outside off, padded away
comes down the track and works it to right of midwicket
again takes one on the pad
fuller, closer to the off stump and defended
spins in from outside off, tries to whip it away to the on side, misses and is struck on the pad. Going down leg side, though.
bad start: full and drifting down the leg side, tickled to fine leg
122. 8 kmph full and on the middle stump line, coming in a touch, defended to the leg side
clean drive down the ground. Caressed away. It was full pitched and he drove it between the bowler and the mid-on fielder.
shifts his line to outside off stump and Taylor lets it go past him
cuts in a touch from outside off, defended on the front foot. Rauf's no-ball problems mount, though.
short delivery and is pulled away
pushed through the on-side field. 11 runs in this over.
turns in sharply from outside off and he is rather late in deciding to play; bottom-edges an intended cut
leans forward to drive to long-off
Taylor prefers to drive with the turn and picks up a single to long-on
spins towards the pads and clips it enroute to the 'keeper
slightly short and punched to long-on
spinning down leg and again strikes him on the pad
punched through the off side
floated outside off, thrashed to long-on
way outside the off stump, left alone
leg break, turns sharply  but starts from outside off stump
beaten. again starting outside off stump and Taylor tries to cover drive
flighted but too full and is driven to long-on for a single
floated on the off stump, defended on the front foot
on the leg and middle, flicked away to fine leg
leans forward to drive to long-off for a single
leans forward to defend
leans forward to flick to square leg.
on the middle and leg, worked to right of backward square leg

Dropped: Fawad spills one over his head at cover, Rizwan lands it short and wide outside off, he slashed hard and Fawad drops it, we nearly have a run out as the non-striker just makes his ground, Rizwan fails to gather the ball cleanly from the deep
flighted outside off, pushed to long-off
slides on the pads, turned to the on side
pitches short, poor delivery, Taylor feasts on the half tracker by pulling with intent over midwicket
flighted outside off, pushed towards mid-off
flighted outside off, lands on a fullish length, turned towards point
just a touch too wide outside off, allows Taylor to rock back and cut to the deep
tossed outside off, gets forward and drives to deep cover
rocks back and plays with an open face of the bat to cover
fullish outside off, in the slot to drive, he pushes firmly to cover
another half tracker, this time Taylor flat bats it to long-on
pitches outside off, cut to point
tossed outside off, big full toss, he slashes hard but can't beat mid-off
flighted outside off, cut to deep point
pitches on off and middle, he turns his wrists and works it to the on side
flighted outside off, left alone
full and wide outside off, he stretches out and beats the diving Malik at extra cover, in fact it was a midfield
pushed to the off side with soft hands, good running, Rizwan isn't quick enough with the throw
dabbed to the off side, quick single taken
beaten..that ball straightens outside the off stump, squares him up completely, good comeback by Fawad
gives it a bit of air outside off, gets it to spin, bounce and beat the outside edge, good ball
flighted outside off, pushed to the off side
flighted outside off again, gets forward and beats point
great stroke, flighted outside off, he gets in position early for the slog sweep and slams that past midwicket
good comeback, pitches on a good length outside off and gets it to turn, he pokes at it
pushed too wide outside off, he shoulders arms
better line, pitches on off and turns away, he wisely lets it go
pitches outside off and turns, punched to mid-off
gives him width outside off, punched behind square on the off side
flighted outside off, pushed to cover
gets forward, covers his stumps, turns it to the on side and sets off for a quick single
opens the face of the bat and glides it to the off side
pushed in flatter and faster, pushed firmly to mid-on
outside off stump, cut to deep point
again a touch short, another cut past point
on the off stump, tapped close on the off side for a single
short-pitched delivery, dabbed to third man
around the off stump, defended on the front foot
outside off stump, pushed to extra covers
a touch short, steered past point for a single
slows up the pace and the batsman is beaten on the drive
fuller and is driven to sweeper cover for a single
floated on the off stump and Taylor paddles it away
full and outside off, left alone
short of length, around the off stump and Taylor smartly drops it close on the off side and they take the single.
full pitched outside off, square driven but straight to point
full again and again driven to that man at point. The sparse crowd are enjoying the game. Making some noise. It's pretty cold out there. Jumpers, sweaters and shawls on view.
Here comes the Riaz bouncer - he bowls at least one per over - and the batsman ducks. Just in time.
a touch short in length and pushed to point
floated on the off stump, defended down the track
and again
flighted full, almost at the blockhole, dug out to right of the bowler who moves smartly to stop
outside off, driven to covers. Sarfraz screams, "Bahut Aala bahut Aala"

And it's really bahut aala (very nice) from both the bowler and the 'keeper. Fawad slowed it up, tossed it up a little more, drew the batsman forward before turning it past the bat and Sarfraz did the rest. A useful partnership of 85 runs comes to an end.
floated on the off stump line, driven to long-on for a single and Taylor has reached his fifty. Very well played sir.
on the middle stump line, driven to long-on

Big turn to terminate Taylor's resistance. It pithched a foot outside off stump, Taylor went back and was surprised by the sharp turn that saw the ball rush through his bat and pad. Timber! Just before Malik started his run-up, Sarfraz had chirped, "No 7 No 7  boys"
leans forward, reaches the pitch and drives to long-off for a single
almost stumped. It landed outside leg stump, caught the batsman on the lunge and turned past him but clipped the back pad and went towards slips. Else, Sarfraz would have stumped him
outside leg, turned behind square leg
stays round the stumps for the left-handed batsman, on the middle, worked to midwicket
on the middle and leg, turning down and he is struck on the pad
fuller, outside off, driven to long-on for a single
top-edges a sweep shot to fine leg
full and straight, driven to deep midwicket.

And then there were two. Mis understanding and a run out. He leaned forward and tapped a ball close on the off side. Yes and no and yes and by that time, Sarfraz had rushed after the ball, thrown his right glove, lunged at the ball and he fired in a throw to Malik.
full, too full perhaps and is driven to long-off
flighted outside off, pad and bat close together and he defends
floated outside off and Price goes for a sweep shot.
lands outside leg stump and the left-handed batsman pushes it to the on side
outside leg again and Debengwa opts for the sweep shot
full and just outside off, Price tries another sweep but gets an inside-edge on to the pad
gets a leading edge down the track as he tries to work it to on side
outside off and again Price goes for a sweep. There was a noise and Sarfraz goes up in appeal.
another faulty sweep but profitable. He gets a inner edge that takes the ball to fine-leg boundary
shortens the length, pushes it through quicker. punched back to the bowler
drifts in, lands on the middle and off and turns past the defensive jab
slower one, on the off and middle, turned to backward point region
low full toss, driven to covers
overpitched, driven to long-off. Yet another no-ball from Rauf.
yorker ends up as a low full toss, swatted to sweeper covers
slower one, on the legs, tucked past square leg
dropped by Riaz. Tough one, though. It was driven towards long-off and Riaz ran in, swooped low but couldn't hold on.
another slower one, again on the legs and is tickled away for a single
fullish, dug out and driven to long-on for a single
short and is punched to long-off
shuffles across to the off stump and works a delivery on middle past square leg
Price keeps going for his sweep shots. No luck again though. Sarfraz collects.
full and just outside off, driven hard but straight to Fawad
on the legs, turned to on side
full toss, on driven to long-on
gets his yorker right but then it's a no-ball. Another free hit coming up
full pitched, driven to sweeper cover
yorked! Around 130 kmph, full and straight at the off stump, hint of late movement in and Price has a stab and a miss.

Yorked again! Raufed up! This one swung in a bit more than the previous delivery and went past the jab to crash into the off stump. In a nice gesture, the Pakistani fielders ask Wahab Riaz and Rauf to lead them back to the pavilion.

inn2.comm: gets off the mark with a clip past square leg.
again on the pads, tucked to fine leg for a single. Slight fumble there but Brent recovers to fire in the throw
What a way to start your international career. It was short in length, just outside off stump, he hopped up and punched on the up through cover point
moves towards the line and steers to point
beaten! It pitched on a length, around off stump, luring Khurram forward before leaving him.
he has the guts. Charges down the track and drives. Mistimes it to mid-off and rushes across for a quick single. Had it hit, he might have been out, though. Adrenalin rush.
shaping away from the batsman who withdraws his bat in time
shuffles a touch, covers his off stump and lets the ball zip past the off stump. The crowd have come in greater numbers now.
swing and a miss. A touch short in length and he tries to beat the hell out of the leather and misses. Went too hard at it.
stands up tall and punches to covers.
picks up his second four. It was drifting on to the pad and he went back to wrist it  to fine leg boundary.
cuts in a touch, gets behind the line to play towards mid-on
on the off stump line, driven to covers
on the middle and off line, pushes it back to the bowler
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket.
pushes it wide outside off stump
in the zone outside off stump, Nasir flashes at it but can't connect
closer to the off stump and is pushed to covers
lands on a length, outside off and veers away; left alone
pitches outside off, straightens and Khurram lets it go
leans forward, gets close to the line of the delivery on middle and off and on drives to right of mid-on. He then practises playing that shot straight.
on the pads, clipped past square leg
beaten. Fullish, outside off stump and Manzoor is beaten on the drive. A touch late in getting across
is more cautious this time and pushes a similar delivery to covers
short in length and whipped to left of short midwicket but a good tumbling stop there prevents them from taking a run
length delivery on the stumps, nudged to the on side
crashed through point. Short and wide and he bisected the region between point and covers
fuller and Nasir drives hard but straight to mid-off
on a length, angling away from Nasir who runs it down to third man
on the middle stump line, worked to fine leg for a single
short in length, extra bounce and Khurram hops to get on top of the bounce and punches it down on to the ground and to short cover
outside off stump, dabbed to third man
on the off stump line, a slight sideways shuffle and he punches it to covers
Thwack!  He waits on the short-of-length delivery around the off stump before punching it through covers. The bottom-hand punch doing the trick.
on the middle and leg,  worked past the diving midwicket fielder
banged in short but Nasir is ready; he swivels and unfurls a neat pull shot
short of length and this time it's Nasir' turn to punch on the up and through covers. He is taller than Khurram and so he doesn't hop, just stands tall and knives through the line.
Collision between mid-on and mid-off but the mid-off fielder - Debengwa- holds on to it. It was a slog from Nasir but only managed to send the ball straight up.
short of length, cutting in from just outside off, Younis moves towards the line and dead-bats
outside off, left alone. Hmm... wide called. Chugumbura knocked the bails off at release and that must have caused him to slip it wider
closer to the off stump and Younis Khan lets Taibu come into play
outside off and Younis plays his typical slash down to third man
just outside off, Khurram tries to punch it away but ends up mistiming it
on the stumps, pushed away
full and straight, nudged to midwicket. Meanwhile, in the stands, some people have climbed on to the roof. hmm! Fiddler on the roof
full pitched, driven down the track
even fuller and Younis drives to left of mid-on for a single

outside off stump and Khurram covers his off stump and shoulders arms. When the ball has been on a length and outside off, he has left them. Not a bad sign. Only when it has been short of length, he has tried to punch them through covers.
full and driven to mid-on
drifts to the pads and Khurram Manzoor flicks it for a boundary
pushed to left of mid-off, Younis wants a run but Khurram sends him back
fab square drive. It was a touch short, just outside off and Younis rocked back to play his whippy square punchy drive through cover point
straighter and Younis plays it to mid-off
slightly short of length, mistimes a drive to covers
leans forward and steers a fuller delivery to point
wide down the leg side and Taibu can't reach
just outside off stump, guided to left of backward point and they rush across for a quick single
walks across and forward, then he stops before on driving to right of mid-on for a single.
slower one, full and Manzoor shuffles across, waits before driving to covers
length delivery outside off, Manzoor shuffles across, then plants his back leg across and square drives to point
full and outside off stump, left alone
yet another slower one and Manzoor is caught on the shuffle, arrests his sideways movement and jabs it away
on the off stump, pushed to covers
fabulous square drive. Hit with a typical Younis flourish. Full and outside off, he planted his left foot across and cracked it
Innovation. He walks outside off stump, all three sticks visibile, reaches a full delivery outside off and lofts it straight. Absolutely straight.
three in a row. The bowler drags this one short and Younis pulls it over midwicket
outside off, again that walk across and he steers to point
defended on the front foot
full and defended on the front foot.
a touch short and he punches it to sweeeper cover
well outside off, Manzoor tries to dab it away but can't reach. Taibu is standing up to the stumps now
on driven to midwicket
slower one, full and defended back down the track
length delivery on the middle, worked to square leg
well outside off and Manzoor retains the strike by running it down to third man
a touch short and Manzoor went back to punch it to long-off
on the middle and Younis sweeps it to short fine leg
and again. Not a sweep, more of a wristy turn of the bat
And he brings out his favourite reverse sweep. On the stumps and swept past backward point
landed outside leg stump, turned in and Younis took it on the pad
fuller and Younis flicks it for a single
full and outside off, Younis tries a late-cut and Taibu, standing up to the mediumpacer, gathers
that walk again. He moved outside off - Taibu moved with him behind - and he fetched a short delivery from outside off and pulled it to the midwicket boundary
And again - both Younis and Taibu move! - but the ball is fuller and outside off, driven to covers
the bowler is clearly upset with all this movement. Not off the track but by the batsman and sends down a full toss. Drilled down the ground.
yet again he walks outside off and drives to long-off. Both the batsman and the bowler have a laugh and Younis puts his hand on the bowlers' shoulder.
on the middle and leg, turned to right of square leg
leans forward to defend a flighted delivery from round the stumps
again pushed to the off side
tossed up, outside off, steered to backward point. So far, he has shown restraint against the spinner
on the middle and leg, wristed behind square leg for a single
full and on the legs, flicked for a single.
gift-wraps a boundary. Left-arm spin from round the stumps, he sends down a long-hop and Younis pulled it to the boundary
again short and this time knived to wide long-off
on the stumps, dabbed to covers
back to short stuff and Younis went back to work it to deep midwicket
errs on the shorter side again and the young Khurram carves it past mid-on.
again he lands it short - don't know what's happening out there, is it that cold?! - cut powerfully by Khurram past backward point.
turned and he was beaten but adjusted quickly by moving his hands and jabbed it to backward point
pulls out another reverse sweep
on the off stump line, not much turn, worked behind square leg for a quick single
bit more air and Manzoor lunged forward to defend. The ball beat the pad and strikes the pad. Going down leg, though
goes back to drop the ball close to the leg side, wants a single but Younis is not in a suicidal mood.
from wide of the crease, from round the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
down the leg side, struck on the pad
again on the legs, tickled past square leg
lands on a length, outside leg stump, turns and Manzoor pokes at it and gets an leading edge
outside leg stump, turns in, allows it to spin before punching it to long-off
on the off stump line, steered to backward point
on the leg stump line, worked to short midwicket
leans forward to defend
and again. Pushed to the off side.
on the middle and leg, turned to the leg side. He has been circumspect against the spinners; wants to stay there till the end. A good sign.
on the off stump line, leans forward to defend
tossed up and defended on the front foot

brings up his fifty with a boundary to fine-leg region. It is his 31st ODI fifty and 7th against ZImbabwe. It has been a breezy knock. Faras reminds me that, "Younis Khan's average against Zimbabwe has just crossed the 50-mark."

turns away from Manzoor who jabs at it and gets an outside edge. If anything he has looked a bit iffy while defending against the spin. ie if i have to be harsh and pick some thing. There have been three occasions when has got the leading edge, closing his bat-face a touch early. But this is just a casual observation.
not when he is attacking. Rocks back, makes room and creates length to force it through extra cover
leans forward and turns it to square leg
gets a bottom-edge on an attempted reverse sweep but would pick three more runs, down to fine-leg region
down the track and he mistimes a lofted shot over mid-on but it falls safely
tickles a delivery on the middle and leg, to square leg region
hurries him with a quicker one and he defends
beaten completely! It drifted in from round the stumps, landed on the middle and off, gripped and spun past the defensive poke. Fab delivery.
in with the arm and defended on the front foot. Younis had gone across for a chat after the previous delivery.
on the back foot to defend. Price runs on and has a word with the batsman.
forced through the off side
tapped to cover point and they take a single
leans forward to defend
outside leg stump and he goes back to work it to deep midwicket
poor delivery. Too short but Younis fails to put it away. He mistimed his pull shot to deep midwicket
retains the strike with a quick single to the off side
on the middle stump line, worked to square leg
leans forward to defend
slow through the air, Khurram rocks back to punch it powerfully to long-off
goes back to defend a delivery to short midwicket

Masakadza takes a skier. Price went wide of the crease this time, from round the stumps and flighted across a loopy delivery outside off. Younis Khan went down on his knee and attempted a slog-sweep but top edged it towards long-off. Well taken by Masakadza
flighted outside off, with a silly-point and slip in, defended on the front foot
short and pulled to long-on for a single. Had he got it a tad wider, he could have added three more runs
from over the wickets and offers width and length and Khurram accepts both and carves it past point
on the middle and leg, turned past square leg for a single
lands outside leg stump, turns in and defended to the on side

flighted on the middle and leg and Khurram brings up his fifty on his debut with a drive to long-on. The cap comes off, the long hair bobs in the air as he lifts his bat towards the dressing room where all the players give him a standing ovation. Good start.
goes back to turn it towards long leg
goes back to push to covers.
arm-ball and he is almost trapped but manages to bring the bat down to keep it out
leans forward to glance a full delivery on the middle and leg

cleans him up. Right after fifty, he went for a sweep and is gone. It was full and on the off stump, too full to play that hard sweep and it went under the bat and on to the off stump. Price is chuffed up; he really wanted Khurram's wicket, had beaten him on a few occasions. And finally does him in with a straighter one.
shuffles across and turns a full delivery to midwicket
outside off and pushed to covers
leans forward to defend a delivery on the middle stump line
turns in from outside leg, wristed past the short fine-leg fielder
Bad delivery. Another gift. Really short and the left-handed Fawad pulls it to deep midwicket boundary.
goes back to punch straight to covers where there is a rare misfield by an Zimabwean player  - Maruma
leans forward, turns a flighted delivery to mid-on
moves outside leg stump and the bowler follows him but he moves even further and cuts it to deep point
slow through the air, lands outside off, past the defensive prod and strikes the pad
plays a compact forward defensive stroke this time
flighted outside off, dabbed away
a tad flatter and perhaps, a touch quicker, defended down the track
bit of width offered outside off and Fawad forces it through covers
on the middle stump line, turned behind square leg for a single
fullish, outside off, driven to covers
short in length and punched to extra covers.
slower one and Misbah is caught on the walk. Gets a thickish edge to point
another short delivery and gets the treatment it deserved. Pulled to midwicket boundary.
full pitched, driven straight and Brent stops it on his follow through
shout for lbw but he got an inside-edge on it. It was full, hint of shape in and he pushed hard at it
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket . 16 to win
on the off stump line, Misbah was beaten in the flight but adjusts to push it out to point. Price lets out a cry of agony
on the middle and leg, gets off the strike with a nudge behind square leg
outside off stump and defended solidly
outside off stump, not all that short but Fawad cuts it on the width and forces it away to the point boundary
on the off stump line, dabbed to the on side. Price thought it hit the pad first and lets out a stifled appeal
on the legs and Misbah helps himself to another boundary with a flick
shifts his line to just outside off and is defended to covers
short in length and played towards cover. He wanted to force it through cover point as he is seen practising that shot afterwards.
steers this length delivery to backward point.
full and straight and he respects the line and length by defending
slower one, on the pads, turned past square leg for a single. How many last-ball singles has Misbah taken? Hmm..!
goes back to work it to midwicket. Again he wanted to turn it towards square leg,didn't quite get his wrists working well
wide down the leg side. 5 more runs now.
slows up the pace and shifts his line to outside off, pushed to covers

lands on the off and middle , turns ever so slowly and Misbah tries to turn it to leg side but there is no pace to work with and the ball just rolls in front of him. Price has a big smile- he has really bowled well today, changing his pace constantly and varying the angles
almost got his man. Misbah went for a slog sweep and got a edge but it doesn't carry to backward point
makes room and lofts over mid-off. The scores are level
again he moves outside leg stump, Price sends in a full toss which is flat-batted over long-off. A white wash. This is the fourth time Pakistan have swept a five-match series.
